JOHANNESBURG - The Topbet manager who ordered a strip search of female employees, has been fired.
	
	She had ordered a cleaner to check which of the women at the Germiston branch was on her period. This after blood stains were found in the toilets. WATCH: Women allegedly forced to strip over menstruation claims speak out Employee Gladys Radebe has laid charges of sexual harassment with police. She told eNCA the incident has left her and her family traumatised. eNCA